                "category": "defensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>The carnival bear might respond to commands even while hostile or unfriendly. If it's hostile or unfriendly, use the following degrees of success instead of the usual check results for attempts to @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.Item.Command an Animal] against the bear.</p><hr /><p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The bear does as commanded on its next turn.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The bear hesitates and does nothing on its next turn.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The bear attacks the creature attempting to command it on its next turn.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The bear attacks the creature attempting to command it on its next turn, and becomes immune to Command an Animal for 1 minute.</p>"
